  Article(title="Privacy Policy" :custom-sized="true")
    p This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, process, use, share, and protect your personal information and explains how your Personally Identifiable Information’ (PII) is used online. It applies to Winoutt's collection of information on our website, app, services, and tools (collectively, our "service(s)"). This Privacy Policy applies to our services, which include the website&nbsp;
      a(href="https://winoutt.com/") https://www.winoutt.com/
      | , and our mobile application (“app”). We will not use or share your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy. Please remember that we may have a varied base of users, customers, and clients, as well as companies, firms, startups, small and large businesses, schools, colleges, institutes, and other related fields. This Privacy Policy only applies to our own data practices, and not to the practices of third parties that we do not control.
    p By accessing and using the Services, you agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to any of the provisions as set hereunder in this Privacy Policy, you have no right to use the services. This Privacy Policy should be read together with the Terms of Use and together they constitute the entire agreement between you and us.
    h4 SECTION 1- APPLICABILITY
    p This Privacy Policy applies to any and all Personal Information that we may collect online including, without limitations, through our emails and/or by using any of our services.
    p By using our services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Use. All references applicable to a “User,” as defined in the Terms of Use, apply to you. For purposes of this Privacy Policy, “you” may mean the representative of a company, firm, business, or an institute who purchases any of our services, an account administrator, an owner of a startup or business, the parents or guardian of a kid or a child, or an adult or a supervised minor that uses the services purchased by a company or a firm to communicate with and participate in programs of such company.
    h4 SECTION 2- PERSONAL INFORMATION COLLECTION
    p The information we collect may include a variety of personal data collected about our users so we can provide you with the best user experience. Some of the information that is collected may be automatically collected via the different protocols that have been introduced over the years.
    p You may have to provide us with information about yourself, like your first and last name, phone number, email, contact details, and in case of the phone app, the information related to phone identity as well as certain permissions for the proper usage of the app. You may also need to provide information in the shape of descriptions, notes, and comments when you upload, submit your content to us.
    h4 SECTION 3- COOKIES AND DATA COLLECTION POLICY
    h6.font-weight-bold 3.1. What is a Cookie?
    p
      | Our website&nbsp;
      a(href="https://winoutt.com/") https://www.winoutt.com/&nbsp;
      | doesn’t use cookies directly, however, we may use services through which the cookies may be used on your computer or device. A cookie is a file containing an identifier that is sent by a web server to a web browser and is stored by the browser. The identifier is then sent back to the server each time the browser requests a page from the server. Cookies may be either “persistent” cookies or “session” cookies: a persistent cookie will be stored by a web browser and will remain valid until its set expiry date unless deleted by the user before the expiry date; a session cookie, on the other hand, will expire at the end of the user session, when the web browser is closed. Cookies do not typically contain any information that personally identifies a user, but personal information that we store about you may be linked to the information stored in and obtained from cookies.
    h6.font-weight-bold 3.2. Cookies & Data are Collected Automatically
    p We may collect some information when you use Winoutt (website & app) and use our services. For example, when you visit our website we may send one or more cookies to your computer that identifies your browser and lets us help you to log in faster and enhance your navigation through the site. A cookie may also convey information to us about how you use the service (e.g., the pages you view, the web-links you click, how often you access the service, and other actions you take on the service), and allow us to track the usage of your account on our service over time. This only helps us to make your experience better and gives us insights on how to improve our service quality for the future. We may also collect log files that contain information about your browser or mobile device each time you log in to access the service. The information in the log file may include information, such as, your web request, Internet Protocol ("IP") address, the type of browser you use, information about your mobile phone device, referring / exit pages and URLs, number of clicks and how you communicate with the links on the service, domain addresses, pages viewed, and other such information. The information allows us for more accurate reporting and improvement of the service.
    h6.font-weight-bold 3.3. Data and Google Analytics
    p Data analytics is the science of examining data and conclusions from that information by applying algorithms to derive insights. Thus, to do that, we may also collect analytics data, or use third-party analytics tools, such as Google Analytics to help us measure traffic data and user’s trends for the services. This software and tools may collect information that is sent by your browser or cellphone, including the trends you have been associating with, visited pages, your use of third-party APIs, and other information that assists us in analyzing and improving the service.
    p When you access our services by or through phone and app, we may receive or collect and store a unique identification number associated with your phone, mobile network, device type (cellphone, tablet, etc.) and manufacturer, your phone number, and, depending on your phone settings, your geographical location data, including GPS coordinates or similar information regarding the location of your mobile phone.
    p We may use this data collected through cookies and phone usage, log file, device identifiers, location data, and clear gifs information to:
      ol(type="a")
        li remember this information so you will not have to re-enter and re-login every time you visit or use our services;
        li provide custom, personalized information, and content, including pop-up messages and notifications;
        li monitor our service and find out how effective it is;
        li monitor traffic reports and visitors’ information and finding out the key demographics patterns to see the global usage of our services and its contents;
        li diagnose or fix problems that are related to our services; and
        li other work that may enhance the quality of our service.
    h6.font-weight-bold 3.4. Links
    p Since this is a social networking platform. This site may contain links to other websites. Please note that Winoutt is not responsible for the content, material, data collection, and privacy matters of those linked websites. For that, you need to read their privacy policies and rules when you visit those websites.
    h6.font-weight-bold 3.5 How can Cookies be Disabled?
    p You can disable cookies by following the links below depending on your browser:
    p
      | For Edge,&nbsp;
      a(href="https://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/insider/forum/insider_internet-insider_spartan-insiderplat_pc/how-to-view-and-manage-cookies-in-microsoft-edge/67b3a495-554e-4f1d-995e-93d0ea6882a6") click here
      br
      | For Internet Explorer,&nbsp;
      a(href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/278835/how-to-delete-cookie-files-in-internet-explorer") click here
      br
      | For Mozilla Firefox,&nbsp;
      a(href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences") click here
      br
      | For Google Chrome,&nbsp;
      a(href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647") click here
      br
      | For Safari,&nbsp;
      a(href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT201265") click here
    p Below are links to information about managing your cookie preferences in common browsers:
    ul
      li
        a(href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=en") Google Chrome Cookies
      li
        a(href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences?redirectlocale=en-US&redirectslug=Enabling+and+disabling+cookies") Mozilla Firefox Cookies
      li
        a(:href="`https://support.microsoft.com/en-gb/help/17442/windows-internet-explorer-delete-manage-cookies#ie=ie-11-win-7`") Internet Explorer Cookies
      li
        a(href="https://support.apple.com/kb/PH19214?locale=en_US") Safari Cookies
      li
        a(href="https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/6004245") Google Analytics
    h4 SECTION 4- SHARING OF INFORMATION
    p We do not and will not sell information to others. However, we may share your information with third-party websites and service providers. These service providers may include, but are not limited to, hosting companies, database providers, security service providers, payment processors. The information will be shared only to provide our services to you. Whenever we share information of any kind with any third-party site or service provider, that service provider and site is bound by a contract with us and is in charge of safeguarding your information.  Furthermore, as the business and website grow, we may buy or sell business and assets. Clients, customers, user databases, emails, and visitor information come under such business assets.
    h4 SECTION 5- INFORMATION ACCESS AND USER CONTROL
    p We do not provide services that include any adult, illicit, or sexually explicit content nor do we advertise on adult websites. Any data related to adult content is deleted immediately without any notification.
    p We do not knowingly facilitate any content that is exploitative, discriminatory, hateful, deceptive, or abusive, and our process for doing this is audited annually.
    p If you find any explicit or adult material on the Winoutt website, you may contact us immediately. Sometimes the AI software is unable to scan and remove the adult content automatically. On receiving the report of any adult content, we will remove the adult and explicit material immediately after verification.
    h6.font-weight-bold 5.1 How to Opt-Out of Information Collection
    p If you, as a user, choose to, you can opt-out of having any information collected and having other such contact from us at any time. Please make sure to write us an email or contact us through our website.
    h6.font-weight-bold You can choose to:
