      li Have us delete any data we may have about you.
      li Change or correct data we may have about you.
    h4 SECTION 6- NOTICE FOR RESIDENTS IN THE EUROPEAN ECONOMIC AREA REGARDING STORAGE OF DATA
    p All information you provide to us is stored securely and treated with care and respect.
    p The data that we collect from you may be transferred to and stored at, a destination outside the European Economic Area ("EEA") such as the United States. It may also be processed by persons operating outside the EEA. If we do send your data outside the EEA, we will take reasonable steps to ensure that the recipient implements appropriate measures to protect your information. By submitting your details, you agree to this transfer.
    h4 SECTION 7- GENERAL DATA PROTECTION REGULATIONS (GDPR) & CalOPPA COMPLIANCE
    p If you are a citizen of any European country or state or if you are a resident of the state of California, the following disclosure is made in compliance with the European General Data Protection Regulations and The California Online Privacy Protection Act (CalOPPA).
    p You have the right to access the personal information about you that we store on our systems, and have us update, correct, or delete it. In addition, you may at any time withdraw your consent to any activity in which you provided us your consent. You are also entitled to obtain from us, your information (excluding data we obtained from other sources) in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format, and have the right to transmit those data to another data controller. If you wish to exercise any of these rights, contact us at&nbsp;
      a(href="mailto:admin@winoutt.com") admin@winoutt.com
    h4 SECTION 8- PRIVACY OF CHILDREN’S AND PARENT’S ACCOUNTS IN COMPLIANCE WITH COPPA
    p
      span.font-weight-bold COPPA&nbsp;
      | means&nbsp;
      span.font-weight-bold The Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act
      | . This act was enacted in 1998 and under this act; all the necessary steps have been made to protect the information for children, specifically for children under 13. The main focus of the COPPA act is to put parents in control of the information which their children may have access to. Our website and app do not knowingly collect information from children who are under 13 years of age. And we do not knowingly collect, store, maintain, or use personally identifiable information from kids or children under age 13. If you are under 13, you should never provide us with any personal information, nor should you be using our website and our services.
    h6.font-weight-bold PRIVACY NOTICE DISCLOSURE FOR PARENTS REGARDING WINOUTT APP USAGE BY KIDS UNDER 13
    p We support the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (“COPPA”) and other frameworks like the General Data Protection Regulation (“GDPR”). Our goal is to minimize the information gathered from and disseminated about children, while permitting them to actively participate with the trustworthy information, education, and independent voice for which we are known.
    p In order for your kid to use the Winoutt app and services, he/she will require your permission to use our app and services. Along with that, we will require the parent’s email address, which we use to ask for that parent’s consent.
    h6.font-weight-bold How May Parents Access, Change, or Delete Information about their Kids?
    p If you are a parent, we will need your consent for the processing of your kids’ personal information if you:
    ol(type="a")
      li wish us to cease further collection of personal information from your Children;
      li believe your Children are participating in an activity on the Site that uses their personal information without the parental consent required by law;
      li wish us to make no further use of, or delete, the personal information we have collected online from your Children; and/or
      li
        p no longer wish for your kid to participate as the user of our app,
        h6.font-weight-bold
          u we will delete your Child’s Profile, and any parental contact information we may hold, on request.
    p Note: We will need the same e-mail account and confirmation from the e-mail which was used to create your kids’ account on our app. This step has been taken to improve the security of our app and services.
    h4 SECTION 9- DECLARATION REGARDING CAN-SPAM ACT (2004)
    p The CAN-SPAM Act is a law that sets the rules for commercial email and newsletters and establishes requirements for commercial messages, gives recipients the right to have emails stopped from being sent to them, and spells out tough penalties for violations.
    h6.font-weight-bold a) We collect your email address to:
    p Communicate with you about our events including, but not limited to, notifications about our event, registration confirmations, and receipts, and for offers for additional products related to your event. We may also contact you with offers for other products or events that our company may offer.
    h6.font-weight-bold b) To Be In Compliance with the CAN-SPAM Act, we agree to the Following:
    p If at any time you would like to unsubscribe from receiving future emails, you can email us at the address or phone number listed under the “Contacting Us” portion of this document and we will promptly remove you from all correspondence. If you wish to opt-out of our mailing list you can do so by contacting us at:&nbsp;
      a(href="mailto:admin@winoutt.com") admin@winoutt.com
      | .
    h4 SECTION 10- HOW DO WE PROTECT YOUR DATA
    p We know that data security is important to you. We use specific safeguards to protect and secure your personal information, data, and content. This goes for both the website and app data protection. We care for and protect your information with extreme caution. However, no security system is unbreakable and thus we cannot guarantee the safety of your personal information. Please refer to our&nbsp;
      router-link(:to="{ name: 'TermsOfUse' }" target="_blank") Terms Of Use
      | .
    h4 SECTION 11- AMENDMENTS AND CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
